<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-06-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-06-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5034/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-06-07T17:00:00-04:00">June 7, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>33. Your despatch No. 1383, May 19. You are authorized to leave with the
                            Foreign Office an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> concerning the
                            pending bill, in which you will express the hope that in any resultant
                            legislation the interests of American citizens in existing corporations
                            will receive adequate protection.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>